{
  "texts": [
    "TreeVul utilizes CodeBERT for source code representation and multiple LSTM encoders to generate predictions across different levels of the CWE hierarchy.",
    "This approach allows TreeVul to offer developers detailed predictions for both high-level and low-level CWE-IDs.",
    "Evaluated on a benchmark encompassing C/C++, Java, and Python, TreeVul enhances the ability to pinpoint and address specific vulnerabilities, thus improving the precision of patch management and supporting more targeted security fixes.Existing deep learning methods for vulnerability detection often only determine whether a program contains vulnerabilities but fail to classify the specific types.",
    "Thus, different from the approaches mentioned above, Zou et al. [280] combined vulnerability detection and type classification into an integrated multi-class detection task.",
    "Specifically, they introduced 𝜇VulDeePecker which introduces the concept of code attention and considers control-dependence when extracting code gadget [123]."
  ]
}